    <text>
        <body>
      
			<p><persName role="author">Abraham deSola</persName> begs to acquaint the<lb/> Editor of the Occident that he is just in receipt<lb/> of the <date>October</date> no. of his journal and perceiving<lb/> that his communication respecting the Jewish<lb/> Child&#39;s First Catechism is not contained<lb/> therein&#44; must express his utter surprise<lb/> that the Ed Occ. should nevertheless yet<lb/> retain the R. I. in hand though requested<lb/> <hi rend="underline">twice</hi> in said communication to return it if<lb/> unable or indisposed to publish it at the required<lb/> time. <persName role="author">ADS</persName> is the more astonished inasmuch<lb/> that the Ed. Occ&#44; in a letter sent to <persName role="author">ADS</persName><lb/> subsequent to receipt of the M. S. dues<lb/> not at all refer to his inability or indisposition<lb/> to print it for this month. Referring<lb/> the Ed. Occ. to his former letter as to what are<lb/> his wishes respecting its publication he takes<lb/> this opportunity of intimating that this notice<lb/> of Ed. Occ&#39;s letter respecting <persName>Mis <sic>Peixottos</sic></persName> book<lb/> will be deferred to a period later than that<lb/> already intimated.</p>
			<p><placeName>Montreal</placeName> <date>3th Tishri 5614</date>.</p>
			<p><date>7<hi rend="sup">th</hi> October 1853</date>.</p>
          
